03Space Launch 101

{/* The Space Capsule */}

The Terminology...

The Space Capsule

A space capsule is an often-crewed spacecraft that uses a blunt-body re-entry capsule to enter the Earth's atmosphere without wings. Our capsule is where you'll spend your timne during the flight. It includes a space gym, cinema, and plenty of other activities to keep you entertained.

{/* The Spaceport */}

The Terminology...

The Spaceport

A spaceport or cosmodrome is a site for launching (or receiving) spacecraft, by analogy to the seaport for ships or airport for aircraft. Based in the famous Cape Canaveral, our spaceport is ideally situatio to take advantage of the Earth's rotation for launch.

{/* The Launch Vehicle */}

The Terminology...

The Launch Vehicle

A launch vehicle or carrier rocket is a rocket-propelled vehicle used to carry a payload from Earth's surface to space, usually to Earth orbit or beyond. Our WEB-X carrier rocket is the mnost powerful in operation. Standing 150 meters tall, it's quite an awe-inspiring sight on the launch pad!
